'''Dolphin Computer Access''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] company based in Worcester that designs, creates and sells [[software]] for people who are [[Blindness|blind]] or have vision and print impairments, [[dyslexia]] and other specific [[Learning disability|learning difficulties]]. The company was set up in 1986 and now has offices in the United Kingdom, [[United States]], [[Sweden]] and [[Norway]].<ref name=IBT>{{cite news|url= http://www.ibtimes.com/prnews/20081116/dolphin-computer-access-announce-their-acquisition-of-software-express-distribution.htm|title= Dolphin Computer Access Announce Their Acquisition of Software Express Distribution|publisher= International Business Times|date= 16 November 2008|accessdate= 28 January 2010}}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Through the use of Dolphin's [[Screen magnifier|screen enlargers]], [[screen reader]]s and [[braille]] output, users can operate word processors, spreadsheets, databases and the [[internet]].<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.tes.co.uk/article.aspx?storycode=349464|title= A touch of high-tech genius|publisher= Times Educational Supplement|first= Sean|last= Coughlan|date= 6 July 2001|accessdate= 28 January 2010}}</ref> The company's customers include [[Microsoft]], the [[Inland Revenue]], the [[BBC]], the [[Royal Air Force]], [[New College Worcester]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rnib.org.uk/insight-online/partial-sight-specialist-computer-magnification|title=RNIB Insight Online Magazine|last=|first=|date=2015-10-14|website=RNIB|publisher=|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> and [[Vodafone]].<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.thenorthernecho.co.uk/business/3874959.World_market_awaits_company/|title= World market awaits company|publisher= The Northern Echo|date= 25 November 2008|accessdate= 28 January 2010}}</ref>

Dolphin's product SuperNova has won the UK [[The WOW! Awards|WOW! award]] for technology in education.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.insight-visionahead.org.uk/tech.html|title= Latest technology|publisher= Insight Visions Ahead|year= 2008|accessdate= 28 January 2010}}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

In 2005 Dolphin worked alongside [[BT plc|BT]] and the [[National Library for the Blind]] to develop a prototype [[text to speech|synthetic voice application]] enabling books, magazines and newspapers to be converted into audio format, thus enabling them to be read by visually impaired computer users.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.sourcewire.com/releases/rel_display.php?relid=20945&hilite=|title= Talking technology to offer new reading matter to thousands|publisher= sourcewire.com|date= 16 March 2005|accessdate= 28 January 2010}}</ref>

In 2008 the company announced a merger with [[Durham, England|Durham]] based Software Express Distribution Limited, a software development company and producer of Guide, a software package which enables [[visual impairment|visually impaired]] users to access [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]].<ref name=IBT/>

