'''Dualin''' is an [[explosive material]] based on [[nitroglycerin]] and [[nitrogen]]ized [[cellulose]] using sawdust or wood pulp. It is inferior to [[dynamite]] and more liable to explosion. Dualin was invented by the [[Prussia]]n chemist Lieutenant Dittmar in April 1869.<ref>{{cite book|title=Statistics of Mines and Mining in the States and Territories West of the Rocky Mountains|last=Raymond|first=Rossiter W.|publisher=United States Commissions of Mining Statistics|page=495|year=1870}}</ref>

